2LU.F.summary: Acconeer AB (publ) develops radar sensors. It offers A1 radar sensor, a high-precision pulsed short-range radar sensor that is delivered as a one chip system in package solution with embedded radio and antenna for detecting various objects at close range with single measurements, as well as continuous sweeps set to any frequency up to 1500 Hz. The company also provides XM122 IoT module, a low power connected radar module with optimized circular form factor; X112, a development kit, which includes a connector board and a radar sensor board for the development of applications; and A1 software development kit that includes radar sensor services, detectors, and application programming interface. Its products are used in robot and drones, mobile and wearables, Internet of Things, power tools and industrial, healthcare and fitness, and automotive applications. Acconeer AB (publ) was founded in 2011 and is based in Lund, Sweden.

9X6.F.summary: JonDeTech Sensors AB (publ) engages in the research and development of IR sensors. It offers thermopiles for use in the mobile industry, as well as in IOT and energy efficiency and safety applications, such as consumer electronics, green technology, medtech, smart homes, and connected cities. The company has an agreement with OFILM Group Co., Ltd. for the development of presence detection module in laptops. JonDeTech Sensors AB (publ) was founded in 2008 and is based in Stockholm, Sweden.

HANZA.ST.summary: Hanza Holding AB (publ) provides manufacturing solutions in mechanics and electronics areas. The company also offers cutting, bending, stamping, welding, and powder coating services for sheet and heavy mechanics; machining services, such as milling, turning, grinding, EMD, and surface treatment; and PCB assembly services. In addition, it provides cable harnesses solutions, including cutting, crimping, and marking, as well as assembly of harnesses based on customer requirements; and system integration and box build assembly services, which include final assembly of systems, testing, delivery to customer stock, and drop shipments to end customers. Further, the company offers gas turbines and offshore applications, as well as provides business advisory services. It operates in Sweden, Finland, Estonia, Germany, Poland, the Czech Republic, and other European countries, as well as in Norway, North America, and internationally. Hanza Holding AB (publ) was founded in 2008 and is headquartered in Stocksund, Sweden.

JDT.ST.summary: JonDeTech Sensors AB (publ) engages in the development and customization of IR sensor detectors. It offers thermopiles for use in mobile phones and IoT solutions, as well as in energy efficiency and safety applications, such as consumer electronics, green technology, medtech, smart homes, and connected cities. The company has an agreement with OFILM Group Co., Ltd. for the development of presence detection module in laptops. JonDeTech Sensors AB (publ) was founded in 2008 and is based in Stockholm, Sweden.

MEAB-B.ST.summary: Malmbergs Elektriska AB (publ) supplies electric materials for contractors, industries, and retailers in Sweden and internationally. Its luminaries products include accessories and spare parts, downlights/spotlights, emergency lighting products, industry luminaries, interior luminaries, lamps, lighting fixtures, outdoor/street fixtures, and transformers and surge products. The company's automation products comprise electric motors, kWh meters, push buttons, relays, contactors and starters, safety and starter switches, and terminal blocks/jumpers. Its installation products include cable trunkings and bridges, dimmers/CEE plugs and sockets, remote switches, fixings and fasteners, junction boxes and cabinets, switches and sockets, fuses and wiring accessories, and transformers and surge protects, as well as MCB's, RCCB'S, etc. The company also offers heating and ventilation products, such as industry fans and heaters, radiators and thermostats, home appliances, water heaters and pumps, bathroom fans, and heating cables. In addition, it provides tools, batteries and door chimes, insulation materials, test equipment and transformers, work clothes, and crimping and accessories, as well as flexible, installation, and power and control cables and wires. Further, the company offers data and networking components, landline telephony, network and low voltage cables, and aerial accessories. Malmbergs Elektriska AB (publ) was founded in 1916 and is headquartered in Kumla, Sweden.

MLT.F.summary: Mycronic AB (publ), together with its subsidiaries, develops, manufactures, and sells production equipment in Europe, the United States, and Asia. The company operates through four segments: Pattern Generators, High Flex, High Volume, and Global Technologies. The Pattern Generators segment provides mask writers to produce advanced photomasks for displays used in cell phones, tablets, TVs, and computer displays, as well as for semiconductors and multi-purpose segment; and measuring machines that provides quality assurance of photomasks. The High Flex segment offers surface mount technology and inspection solutions for the electronics manufacturers. The High Volume segment provides solutions for dispensing adhesives, mounting fluids, and coatings used in the production of modern electronics. The Global Technologies segment offers manufacturing solutions for micro- and opto-electronics, as well as for mounting and testing camera modules with high precision. It also provides systems and system upgrade services; and spare parts and accessories. It sells its products through agents and distributors. The company serves industrial, aerospace, defense, automotive, energy, medical, IT, and telecommunications sectors. It sells its products through agents and distributors. The company was formerly known as Micronic Mydata AB (publ) and changed its name to Mycronic AB (publ) in June 2014. Mycronic AB (publ) is headquartered in TÃ¤by, Sweden.

NCAB.ST.summary: NCAB Group AB (publ), together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and sells printed circuit boards (PCBs). The company offers multilayer, high density interconnect, radio frequency, insulated metal base, flexible, rigid-flex, semi-flex, and double sided PCBs. Its products are used in various applications, including digital cameras, compact medical devices, surgical light, electrical car charging, mirror eye-camera, and other applications. The company serves aerospace and defense, automotive, datacom, industrial, IOT, medical, power and energy, railway, safety-critical, and telecom industries. It operates in Benelux, China, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Italy, Malaysia, North Macedonia, Norway, Poland, Russia, Spain, Sweden, the United Kingdom, and the United States. The company was founded in 1993 and is headquartered in Bromma, Sweden.

NEON.summary: Neonode Inc., together with its subsidiaries, develops optical sensing solutions for contactless touch, touch, gesture sensing, and in-cabin monitoring in the United States, Japan, South Korea, China, and internationally. The company also licenses its technology to original equipment manufacturers (OEMs) and Tier 1 suppliers. In addition, it provides embedded sensors to OEMs, original design manufacturers, and Tier 1 suppliers. Further, the company sells Neonode branded sensor products, such as AirBar products through distributors. Additionally, it provides engineering consulting services. Neonode Inc. was incorporated in 1997 and is headquartered in Stockholm, Sweden.

NILAR.ST.summary: Nilar International AB develops and manufactures stationary energy storage systems. It offers energy storage solutions for various stationary applications, such as storing energy in residential buildings, industrial premises, and commercial buildings. The company sells its products in Sweden, northern Europe, and internationally. Nilar International AB (publ) was incorporated in 2000 and is headquartered in TÃ¤by, Sweden.

NOTE.ST.summary: NOTE AB (publ), together with its subsidiaries, provides electronics manufacturing services in Sweden, Finland, the United Kingdom, Estonia, China, and internationally. The company provides advanced production technology services in close collaboration with customers, such as component selection, developing test equipment, prototyping, and batch production, as well as after-sales services. It also produces PCBAs, sub-assemblies, and box build products. The company primarily serves the medtech, defense, manufacturing, communication, and consumer electronics industries. NOTE AB (publ) was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Kista, Sweden.

OBD.F.summary: Obducat AB (publ) develops and supplies lithography solutions for the use in the production and replication of micro and nanostructures worldwide. It offers SINDRE, a Nano imprint lithography system for industrial production; EITRE, a Nano imprint lithography for research and development purposes; and wet processing systems. The company also provides installation and support services. Its products are used in various applications, such as light emitting diodes (LEDs) and organic LEDs, optical components, MEMS, NEMS, PZT, hard disk drives, displays, photovoltaics, and medical devices. Obducat AB (publ) was founded in 1989 and is headquartered in Lund, Sweden.

PIEZO.ST.summary: PiezoMotor Uppsala AB (publ) develops, manufactures, and distributes micro motors based on piezoelectric materials in Sweden and internationally. The company provides linear and rotary motors, controllers, and starter kits. Its products are primarily used in medical technology, semiconductor, optics, space and defense, and other markets. The company is headquartered in Uppsala, Sweden.

UNIBAP.ST.summary: Unibap AB (publ) supplies vision processing and visual perception solutions in Sweden. The company offers intelligent vision system-70 stereo cameras; optimized development environment kits that allow users to prototype software and develop HDL code for the FPGA, as well as test new upgrades and switching between processing module families; heterogeneous computing modules; and RCab300, a healthcare logistics solution for the autonomous transportation of small goods, such as medications, test samples, and blood products, as well as pulling carts with linen, liquids, food, and sterilized goods. Its products are used in intelligent industrial automation, intelligent 3D vision, unmanned autonomous surveillance, managed surveillance, robot and drone guidance, and machine tooling inspection applications. The company was founded in 2013 and is based in Uppsala, Sweden.
